               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_209-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Risalah-i Tadbir al-Harb.</title>
                     <note>After the main text come two folios with quotations from the Qur'an on the subject of fighting the infidels and a statement of the need to oppose the encroaching Europeans etc. Contains several diagrams of fortifications and siege works. Treatise on the art of war. Translated from a brief work in French composed in A.D. 1704 for Louis XIV by De AUBAN (Vauban?). Translator is anonymous.</note>
                     <incipit>Nahmiduhu wa nusta'inuhu wa nusalla 'ala khair khalqihi</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, ii, p. 427. No other manuscript noted.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Price's bequest is noted in the Journal for 1836, pp. xii-xiv (an obituary notice p. lx).</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
